From: Ray Liu <ray.xy.liu@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 12 May 2026 12:00:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] ARM: airoha: set kernel TEXT_OFFSET to 0x88000 for AN7563/EN7523

The Airoha EN7523 / AN7563 (AArch32) bootloader stack reserves the
first ~256 KiB of DRAM for ATF: BL31 lives in 0x80003000-0x80035000
with adjacent TZRAM pads, ending at 0x80040000 (see
plat/ecnt/en7523/platform_def.h in the en75xx-class ATF source).
Vendor firmware therefore loads the Linux kernel at 0x80088000,
i.e. 0x88000 above the DRAM base, leaving the entire ATF area
untouched and giving an additional headroom band for BL2 / NPU
staging.

With the default ARM TEXT_OFFSET of 0x8000 the kernel is linked
against PHYS_OFFSET + 0x8000 = 0x80008000 but the FIT loadaddr is
0x80088000. CONFIG_ARM_PATCH_PHYS_VIRT then back-computes
PHYS_OFFSET as stext_phys - TEXT_OFFSET = 0x80080000, which
mismatches the DT memory@80000000 node and turns __turn_mmu_on into
a silent jump to nowhere - no earlycon output, no panic. Pinning
TEXT_OFFSET to 0x88000 makes the link offset agree with the
bootloader's load offset so PHYS_OFFSET resolves to 0x80000000 and
matches the DT.

Apply the same offset to ARCH_AIROHA on ARMv7: only the 32-bit
Airoha targets (EN7523, AN7563/AN7552) compile arch/arm/Makefile;
the AArch64 AN7581 / AN7583 use arch/arm64 and are unaffected.

Signed-off-by: Ray Liu <ray.xy.liu@gmail.com>
---
 arch/arm/Makefile | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

--- a/arch/arm/Makefile
+++ b/arch/arm/Makefile
@@ -167,6 +167,8 @@ endif
 textofs-$(CONFIG_ARCH_QCOM_RESERVE_SMEM) := 0x00208000
 textofs-$(CONFIG_ARCH_MESON) := 0x00208000
 textofs-$(CONFIG_ARCH_AXXIA) := 0x00308000
+# Airoha EN7523 / AN7563: leave the first 0x88000 of DRAM to ATF
+textofs-$(CONFIG_ARCH_AIROHA) := 0x00088000
 
 # Machine directory name.  This list is sorted alphanumerically
 # by CONFIG_* macro name.
